Project 2: To-Do List (List + File Handling)
ðŸ“„ Code:
tasks = []

while True:
    print("1.Add Task  2.View Tasks  3.Save & Exit")
    choice = input("Enter choice: ")

    if choice == "1":
        task = input("Enter task: ")
        tasks.append(task)

    elif choice == "2":
        for i, task in enumerate(tasks, start=1):
            print(i, task)

    elif choice == "3":
        with open("tasks.txt", "w") as file:
            for task in tasks:
                file.write(task + "\n")
        break

ðŸ§  Explanation
list stores tasks

append() adds item

enumerate() adds numbering

with open() safely writes file

.txt file saved automatically

ðŸ“Œ Concepts Covered: List, Loop, File Writing

